"{\"uid\": \"christianpost.com-voices-olympics-closing-ceremony-should-convey-frances-apology.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"The Christian Post  To enjoy our website, you will need to enableJavaScriptin your web browser.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 95, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pleaseclick hereto learn how.\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 125, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"CP VOICES do not necessarily reflect the views of The Christian Post.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 196, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 177, \"end\": 195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Christian Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Opinions expressed are solely those of the author(s).\", \"from\": 197, \"to\": 250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France's contributions to intellectual studies in Western thought and culture have been noteworthy.\", \"from\": 252, \"to\": 351, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Western thought\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 is an opportunity to show the world how much France has advanced from the 100 years prior when they hosted the Olympics in 1924.\", \"from\": 352, \"to\": 491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 362, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 408, \"end\": 414, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If that was an objective of the recent Olympics opening ceremony, France deserves a grade of \\\"F\\\" for its indecent portrayal of what the history of culture has treasured.\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 558, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They depicted Leonardo Davinci's Last Supper in drag.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 716, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 677, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2436621565410677e-25, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 696, \"end\": 707, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0679572837018176e-30, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many Christians and Church leaders were offended and rightly so, but I wasn't.\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 795, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 732, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999725574416747, \"rank\": 2.5445844973164908e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Honestly, my reaction was one of pity for France and its organizers.\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 838, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Was that their idea of encouraging a culture of inclusion?\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The lack of artistic discernment of a treasured international and cross-cultural painting reveals how deep France's culture has sunk.\", \"from\": 924, \"to\": 1057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1031, \"end\": 1037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's pitiful.\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024's ceremony splashed opprobrium on Davinci's iconic piece of art by disparaging his traditional depiction that continues to inspire people of all cultures.\", \"from\": 1073, \"to\": 1238, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1073, \"end\": 1083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A depiction that has captured the emotions of art lovers, whether Christian or not.\", \"from\": 1239, \"to\": 1322, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic ceremony's sketch before a watching world challenged the treasured historical value of the Last Supper and mocked the rich traditional heritage of billions.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It crossed the line of decency and civility.\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1536, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Its lewdness was taken to an unprecedented level.\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1586, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the plan of the organizers was to promote inclusion, they could have surely opted for other artistic and entertaining sketches that encouraged conversations among different thinking people.\", \"from\": 1588, \"to\": 1780, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The international backlash from people of every generation, nation, societal status, and political position was fired at the French organizers.\", \"from\": 1781, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1912, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A young journalist,commented astutely: \\\"The West has officially fallen.\\\"\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So how is it that the French failed so miserably?\", \"from\": 1998, \"to\": 2047, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2026, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The artistic director and mastermind behind the flamboyant opening ceremonysaid\\\"religious subversion [had] never been his intention.\\\"\", \"from\": 2048, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Whatever the \\\"intention,\\\" it was not inspirational.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rather, it revealed how ideology can be a force that sacrifices tradition, culture, historical contributions, and civility in order to force an agenda.\", \"from\": 2236, \"to\": 2387, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Globally, commentators were sharp in highlighting how such blasphemous sketches always single out the Christian faith.\", \"from\": 2388, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2490, \"end\": 2499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French organizers have apologized, but it's difficult to believe that such cultured people who are enriched with theological and philosophical heritages failed to anticipate the international condemnations.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2717, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2511, \"end\": 2517, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"How could such an educated and culturally rich nation not foresee such a debacle?\", \"from\": 2718, \"to\": 2799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Consequently, the ceremony's mocking of Christian faith engendered global divisiveness.\", \"from\": 2801, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2841, \"end\": 2850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Note that this was not a sketch prepared for a private audience, though that would have also been questionable by cultured people.\", \"from\": 2889, \"to\": 3019, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This was planned with forethought that the whole world would be watching.\", \"from\": 3020, \"to\": 3093, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Did they care that billions of Christians would be offended by their choice of art?\", \"from\": 3094, \"to\": 3177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3125, \"end\": 3135, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999725574416747, \"rank\": 2.5445844973164908e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Did they care that an iconic painting that is treasured by history would be unfairly critiqued and denigrated?\", \"from\": 3178, \"to\": 3288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How could this have escaped their preparation processes?\", \"from\": 3289, \"to\": 3345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was an obvious mocking of Christian values.\", \"from\": 3347, \"to\": 3393, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3376, \"end\": 3392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999999998995008, \"rank\": 1.0064477482585607e-10, \"text\": \"Christian values\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where it backfired is that the French probably thought that their artistic display would resonate with inclusiveness.\", \"from\": 3394, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3431, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, it caused a backlash and revealed how French culture is progressing inbias.\", \"from\": 3512, \"to\": 3604, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3567, \"end\": 3581, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But France has an opportunity to make its apology real.\", \"from\": 3605, \"to\": 3660, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3609, \"end\": 3615, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has enough time to prepare for the closing ceremony where it can show the world some respect for how the past 100 years have brought diverse cross-cultural appreciation worldwide and growing civil discourse.\", \"from\": 3661, \"to\": 3871, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a Christian, I acknowledge that not everyone believes like me.\", \"from\": 3873, \"to\": 3938, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3878, \"end\": 3887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So this is not simply another writing from a Christian who is whining about how his faith was caricatured.\", \"from\": 3939, \"to\": 4045, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3984, \"end\": 3993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ideologies can be messaged but they must also tolerate counter-perspectives.\", \"from\": 4047, \"to\": 4123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That is a hallmark of French contribution to Western thought.\", \"from\": 4124, \"to\": 4185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4146, \"end\": 4152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4169, \"end\": 4184, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Western thought\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Western_philosophy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As the famous Frenchman Voltaire once quipped, \\\"I disapprove of what you say, but I will defend to death your right to say it.\\\"\", \"from\": 4186, \"to\": 4313, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hopefully, the closing ceremony of Paris 2024 will make an indelible impression that shows respect for the shared center of civility.\", \"from\": 4315, \"to\": 4448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4350, \"end\": 4360, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That would be a remarkable and memorable finale.\", \"from\": 4449, \"to\": 4497, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The French have contributed so much to Western thought and culture that I would be disappointed if that pitiful opening ceremony is what the world remembers from Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 4498, \"to\": 4671, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4502, \"end\": 4508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9924918996100842, \"rank\": 0.007564404359794382, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4660, \"end\": 4670, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3251405931325191e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France still has an opportunity to apologize meaningfully for its parody of Davinci's Last Supper.\", \"from\": 4672, \"to\": 4770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4672, \"end\": 4678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.8810148078154113, \"rank\": 0.10833453505367517, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4758, \"end\": 4769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.0679572837018176e-30, \"text\": \"Last Supper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Last_Supper\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The apology should materialize in its Olympic farewell to the world.\", \"from\": 4771, \"to\": 4839, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marlon De Blasio is a cultural apologist, Christian writer and author ofDiscerning Culture.He lives in Toronto with his family.\", \"from\": 4843, \"to\": 4970, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4843, \"end\": 4849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marlon_Brando\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.626518417912009e-16, \"text\": \"Marlon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marlon_Brando\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marlon_Brando\"}, {\"begin\": 4885, \"end\": 4894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999998620642241, \"rank\": 1.3793588983498432e-07, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 4946, \"end\": 4953, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.2358084734494664e-14, \"text\": \"Toronto\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Toronto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow him atMarlonDeBlasio@Twitter  Our work is made possible by the generosity of supporters like you.\", \"from\": 4971, \"to\": 5075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Your contributions empower us to continue breaking stories that matter, providing clarity from a biblical worldview, and standing for truth in an era of competing narratives.\", \"from\": 5076, \"to\": 5250, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By making a recurring donation or a one-time donation of any amount, you are helping to keep CP's articles free and accessible for everyone.\", \"from\": 5252, \"to\": 5392, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5345, \"end\": 5347, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passionists\", \"score\": 0.9901578673197236, \"rank\": 0.006480576348609844, \"text\": \"CP\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passionists\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Passionists\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hope you will give us another try and check out some other articles.Return to homepage.\", \"from\": 5394, \"to\": 5481, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Christian Post\", \"from\": 5485, \"to\": 5503, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5485, \"end\": 5503, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Christian Post\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Christian_Post\"}]}]}"